# Spring Boot DevTools 🛠️

## 📖 What is Spring Boot DevTools?

**Spring Boot DevTools (Developer Tools)** is a module that improves the development experience by providing features like:

* Automatic Restart
* Live Reload
* Faster Development
* Development-time Configuration

It helps developers avoid manually restarting the application after every code change.

---

# 🎯 Why Use DevTools?

Without DevTools:

❌ Modify Code

❌ Stop Application

❌ Restart Application

❌ Wait for Server Startup

With DevTools:

✅ Save Code

✅ Application Restarts Automatically

✅ Browser Refreshes Automatically

✅ Faster Development

---

# 🌟 Features of Spring Boot DevTools

## 1. Automatic Restart

Whenever you modify and save your code, Spring Boot automatically restarts the application.

```text id="6ucjtm"
Modify Code
      │
      ▼
Save File
      │
      ▼
DevTools Detects Change
      │
      ▼
Application Restarts
```

---

## 2. Live Reload

Automatically refreshes the browser when files change.

Example:

* Modify HTML
* Save File
* Browser Reloads Automatically

---

## 3. Faster Startup

DevTools uses two classloaders:

* Base ClassLoader
* Restart ClassLoader

This makes restart much faster.

---

## 4. Development-Time Properties

DevTools automatically applies useful development settings.

Examples:

* Disable Template Cache
* Enable Debugging
* Faster Development

---

# 📦 Adding DevTools Dependency

## Maven

```xml id="djlwm1"
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-devtools</artifactId>
    <scope>runtime</scope>
    <optional>true</optional>
</dependency>
```

---

## Gradle

```gradle id="djlwm2"
dependencies {
    developmentOnly(
        "org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-devtools"
    )
}
```

